HOOK: Jump to a bookmark instantly — just type its name
HOW: <bookmark_name>  |  CTRL+X+D to list all bookmarks

HOOK: Add or remove a bookmark for the current folder
HOW: CTRL+X+B

HOOK: Open any command without remembering its name
HOW: fa  |  CTRL+X+A — fuzzy search everything

HOOK: Go up one directory without typing cd ..
HOW: CTRL+X+U

HOOK: Navigate subfolders interactively — no typing needed
HOW: CTRL+X+N

HOOK: Snapshot a file before risky changes
HOW: sn FILEPATH

HOOK: Restore a snapshotted file at any time
HOW: re [FILEPATH]  — no argument shows an interactive list

HOOK: Kill a process by name or port, interactively
HOW: ik

HOOK: Mark a folder, come back to it from anywhere
HOW: c  to mark  |  gc  to jump back

HOOK: Mark a file, open it from anywhere in the editor
HOW: cf FILEPATH  to mark  |  gcf  to open

HOOK: Copy the full path of a file to the clipboard
HOW: cpcb [FILEPATH]

HOOK: Copy the directory path of a file to the clipboard
HOW: cpdcb FILEPATH

HOOK: Rename a file by pattern — no mv gymnastics
HOW: rn FILENAME PATTERN [REPLACEMENT]

HOOK: Open the most recently modified file in the current tree
HOW: olf

HOOK: Record a command sequence and replay it with one shortcut
HOW: sr  |  CTRL+P  to start  |  fr  |  CTRL+P+CTRL+P  to stop  |  CTRL+X+X  to replay

HOOK: Re-bind and replay the last recorded macro across sessions
HOW: CTRL+P+CTRL+L

HOOK: Search files by name, get navigate-style shortcuts
HOW: fan PATTERN

HOOK: Search file contents and jump straight to the matching line
HOW: fag PATTERN

HOOK: Add the current directory to PATH permanently
HOW: ap

HOOK: Refresh the current directory listing
HOW: rf

HOOK: Stay in your folder when switching users
HOW: sucd USER

HOOK: Get help on any topic without leaving the shell
HOW: CTRL+X+H — fuzzy search across all help topics

HOOK: Open nixlper.sh for a quick tweak
HOW: CTRL+X+O

HOOK: Delete the current folder safely — no bare rm -rf in history
HOW: CTRL+X+E

HOOK: Delete the current folder contents safely
HOW: CTRL+X+R

HOOK: Toggle size and permission display during navigation
HOW: toggle_navigation_mode
